{"cursor":"3492","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Officeholder |name = Ronald Pofalla |image = Pofalla2002.jpg\n|imagesize = 200px |alt = |caption =\n| office = Federal Minister of Special Affairs and Chief of the Chancellor's\n| Office  term_start = 28 October 2009 term_end = predecessor = Thomas de\n| MaiziÃ¨re successor =\n|office2 = Member of the Bundestag |term_start2 = 1990 |term_end2 = |birth_date\n= |birth_place = Weeze, Northrhine-Westphalia |death_date = |death_place =\n|nationality = |party = CDU |alma_mater = University of Cologne |profession =\nLawyer |religion = |website = [http://www.ronald-pofalla.de/ www.ronald-\npofalla.de] }} 'Ronald Pofalla' (born May 15, 1959 in Weeze) is a German\npolitician, currently serving as the Chief of Staff of the German Chancellery\nand a Federal Minister for Special Affairs in the Second Cabinet Merkel.\n\nFrom 2004 to 2005 he was deputy chairman of the CDU/CSU's parliamentary group\nin the Bundestag, and served as the Secretary General of the CDU from 2005 to\n2009, when he was appointed to cabinet, succeeding Thomas de MaiziÃ¨re as\nChief of Staff.\n\nPofalla studied social pedagogy at the Fachhochschule in Kleve. After finishing\nwith a Diplom in 1981 he studied law at the University of Cologne. In 1991 he\npassed the second Staatsexamen. Since that time Pofalla has been licensed to\nwork as a lawyer.\n\nPofalla has been a member of the CDU since 1975. At first he was engaged in the\nJunge Union. He was chairman of the JU in the State of North Rhine-Westphalia\nfrom 1986 to 1992.\n\nSince 1990 he has been a member of the Bundestag.\n\nRonald Pofalla has been repeatedly criticized for being rude towards other\nrepresentatives of the Bundestag and other secretaries of the German government.\nIn September 2011 he seriously insulted Wolfgang Bosbach, senior group leader of\nthe CDU/CSU-group in the Bundestag after an in-house discussion about the\nenhancement of the European Financial Stability Facility. [http://www.spieg-\nel.de/international/germany/0,1518,789797,00.html Der Spiegel: Merkel Ally Under\nFire for Profanity-Ridden Tirade]\n","linknr":204,"url":"Ronald_Pofalla","recorded":1363600491,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Ronald_Pofalla&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Ronald_Pofalla&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-head","#p-search","/wiki/File:Pofalla2002.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/Pofalla2002.jpg/200px-Pofalla2002.jpg","/wiki/Federal_Minister_for_Special_Affairs_of_Germany","/wiki/German_Chancellery","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/ba/Flag_of_Germany.svg/22px-Flag_of_Germany.svg.png","/wiki/Germany","/wiki/Incumbent","/wiki/Thomas_de_Maizi%C3%A8re","/wiki/Bundestag","/wiki/Incumbent","/wiki/German_federal_election,_1990","/wiki/Weeze","/wiki/Northrhine-Westphalia","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/ba/Flag_of_Germany.svg/22px-Flag_of_Germany.svg.png","/wiki/Germany","/wiki/Christian_Democratic_Union_(Germany)","/wiki/Alma_mater","/wiki/University_of_Cologne","/wiki/Lawyer","http://www.ronald-pofalla.de/","/wiki/Weeze","/wiki/Germany","/wiki/Politician","/wiki/German_Chancellery","/wiki/Federal_Minister_for_Special_Affairs_of_Ger